<br>
     The 2nd thing I looked at was Weaponskill for 50 weapon vs 43 weapon.  I looked at 50+12 vs 43+12.  The difference in weaponskill was 47.  Aug Str 3 increased weaponskill by 56.  With 43+12 and 178 Strength (norse) my weaponskill was 1016.  This is without any RAs.  <br>
<br>
     I believe that if this patch goes live without any further changes, skalds will be greatly hindered by not going at least 44 songsWe're talking about the following:  47 more weaponskill for going 50 weapon while using a 43 dd and 26 dd(which will NEVER EVER land) so basically you're reduced to 1 shout.  Aug Strength 3 will give 56 weaponskill which eliminates the disparity while allowing you to go 50 in Battlesongs without losing anything.  10 RA points is worth the cost, especially since it sets you up to get Mastery of Arms for those slow 2h weapons.<br>
<br>
     This was testing 43 weaponskill, I didn't look at 39 because I'm not convinced a few more points of parry (or parry at all) is ever useful in rvr...getting past people's defense definitely IS useful and that requires higher weaponskill.  If you go 44 Battlesongs, you'll be using a 43dd and 44dd.  This is acceptable, except that it eliminates the ability to go 50 weapon which pretty much removes any interest to spec weapon above 44 (no ragnarok).  <br>
<br>
     I see the new Skald specs as being:<br>
<br>
43 Weapon 50 Songs 2 Parry<br>
44 Weapon 46 Songs 17 Parry<br>
39 Weapon 50 Songs 18 Parry<br>
<br>
     I think the days of the 50 Weapon skald are over. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=extren@teamskald>Extren</A> at: 9/24/03 11:05 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roseannelottsa>Roseanne Lottsa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Skald TL</span><br>  Posts: 418<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/24/03 11:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=707.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Okay, shouts are in!</span><hr size=1> I'm going to have to disagree about 50 Weapon.  If you go to 43 BS and 50 weapon, you will have 2 shouts that are basically what we have right now, pre-1.65 changes.  While they are not great, they are usable and coupled with the fact that you will have 50 Weapon will get the job done IMHO.  It will become a valid spec in my eyes.<br>
<br>
Currently (pre-1.65) if you went 50 Weapon, you would have to use the 34 Shout as your highest shout and 26 as your followup.  Now at least you have a 43 Shout that will be good.<br>
<br>
On the flip-side, 50 BS and 43 weapon is a more valid spec than it was before.<br>
<br>
Personally I wish we could have gotten the second shout at 49 and not 50, which would open up even more varieties (including being able to receive the 44 weapon style and the highest DD shout), but it doesn't seem to be something Mythic is willing to do at this time, unless there is a way to show that it is needed.<br>
<br>
What I am trying to find out is, if a person goes to 50 weapon, does the benefit gained from getting 50 weapon make up for the loss of the BS line.  Also I need to check the reverse, if 50 BS, does the line itself make up for a reduced weapon effectiveness.  That's the best way to gauge if these changes are any good.  Prior to this the answer was a resounding !NO! to both those questions.  Now, I'm not sure.<br>
<br>
Rosey<br>
